@startuml MatchMonitorClassification_Sequence
title Match Monitor Classification - Sequence Diagram (Classify Job)

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam noteBorderColor #FBC02D

actor "Scheduler\n(Every 5 mins)" as Scheduler
participant "ClassificationJobController" as Controller <<HTTP>>
participant "MatchMonitorClassification\nJobService" as JobService
participant "MatchMonitorClassification\nService" as Service
participant "MatchMonitorClassification\nDataAccess" as DataAccess
participant "ProblemAccountServices" as PAService
participant "CustClassToMainDBService" as MainDBService
database "CTS_DataCenter\n(MySQL)" as CTS_DB
database "bodb_VR2Model\n(SQL Server)" as Main_DB

== Job Trigger ==

Scheduler -> Controller: POST /api/classificationJobs/\nClassifyMatchMonitor()
activate Controller

Controller -> JobService: ClassifyMatchMonitor()
activate JobService
note right
  Service Name: "Match Monitor Classication"
  Batch Size: 500 (fixed)
end note

== Step 1: Get ONE Match & Run Detection ==

JobService -> Service: ClassifyMatchMonitor()
activate Service

Service -> DataAccess: ClassifyMatchMonitor()
activate DataAccess

DataAccess -> CTS_DB: CALL CTS_DC_CustClassification_\nMatchMonitor_Classify()
activate CTS_DB
note right
  **Multi-Result Set SP**:
  
  **ResultSet 1**: ClassifyGBMMCustInfosEntity[]
  - CustID
  - SportGroupID
  - CategoryID
  - Reason
  
  **ResultSet 2**: string (MMDetailIDList)
  - Comma-separated IDs of fraud tickets
  - Example: "123,456,789"
  
  **ResultSet 3**: int? (MatchID)
  - Current match being processed
  - NULL if no match in queue
  
  **Logic**:
  1. SELECT TOP 1 match (FIFO)
  2. Run group betting detection
  3. Identify fraud tickets
  4. Extract customer info
end note

CTS_DB --> DataAccess: Return 3 ResultSets
deactivate CTS_DB

DataAccess -> DataAccess: Parse ResultSets
note right
  **Parse into Model**:
  - CustInfos = ResultSet 1
  - MMDetailIDList = ResultSet 2.FirstOrDefault()
  - MatchID = ResultSet 3.FirstOrDefault()
end note

DataAccess --> Service: ClassifyGBMatchMonitorModel
deactivate DataAccess
note right
  **Model Contains**:
  - CustInfos[]
  - MMDetailIDList (string)
  - MatchID (int?)
end note

Service --> JobService: Return Model
deactivate Service

== Step 2: Insert Problem Account (If Has CustInfos) ==

alt Has CustInfos?
    
    JobService -> JobService: Convert to InsertProblemAccountEntity[]
    note right
      **Mapping**:
      - From: ClassifyGBMMCustInfosEntity
      - To: InsertProblemAccountEntity
      
      **Constructor auto-maps**:
      - CustID, SportGroupID
      - CategoryID, Reason, etc.
    end note
    
    JobService -> Service: InsertProblemAccount(entities, config)
    activate Service
    note right
      **Config**:
      - RoleGroup: Member
      - ExternalBatchSize: 500
      - IsUpdateDangerToMainDB: true
      - IsWriteLog: true
      - ServiceName: "Match Monitor Classication"
    end note
    
    Service -> PAService: InsertProblemAccountPackage(\npas, FunctionId, CCInputFlow, ...)
    activate PAService
    note right
      **Inherited from ProblemAccountServices**
      
      **Parameters**:
      - FunctionId: ClassifyGBMatchMonitor
      - CCInputFlow: InsertPACategory
      - IsLogData: false
      - ServiceName: "Match Monitor Classication"
    end note
    
    PAService -> CTS_DB: INSERT/UPDATE CTSCustomerClassification
    activate CTS_DB
    note right
      **Insert Problem Account**:
      1. Validate CustIDs
      2. Check existing classification
      3. Insert/Update CC record
      4. Set CategoryID (CC type)
      5. Mark as PA (IsPA = 1)
      6. Update LastModifiedDate
    end note
    
    CTS_DB --> PAService: Inserted CustIDs[]
    deactivate CTS_DB
    
    PAService --> Service: Return CustIDs[]
    deactivate PAService
    
    == Step 3: Push to MainDB ==
    
    Service -> MainDBService: PushExternalProblemAcountPackage(\nCustIDs, config)
    activate MainDBService
    note right
      **External Push Process**:
      1. Distinct CustIDs
      2. Batch by ExternalBatchSize (500)
      3. Push each batch to MainDB
    end note
    
    loop For each batch (500 CustIDs)
        MainDBService -> Main_DB: PUSH Customer Classification
        activate Main_DB
        note right
          **Sync to External System**:
          - Update customer CC status
          - Update PA flag
          - Update category info
        end note
        
        Main_DB --> MainDBService: Success/Failure
        deactivate Main_DB
    end
    
    MainDBService --> Service: Push Complete
    deactivate MainDBService
    
    Service --> JobService: Return true
    deactivate Service
    
end

== Step 4: Mark Match as Completed ==

JobService -> Service: ClassifyMatchMonitorCompleted(model)
activate Service

alt Has MatchID?
    
    Service -> DataAccess: ClassifyMatchMonitorCompleted(\nmatchID, mmDetailIDs)
    activate DataAccess
    
    DataAccess -> CTS_DB: CALL CTS_DC_CustClassification_\nMatchMonitor_Completed(\nip_MatchID, ip_MMDetailsIDList)
    activate CTS_DB
    note right
      **Mark as Processed**:
      
      **Input**:
      - ip_MatchID: Current match
      - ip_MMDetailsIDList: "123,456,789"
      
      **Update**:
      UPDATE CTSMatchMonitorDetail
      SET IsProcessed = 1
      WHERE ID IN (parse ip_MMDetailsIDList)
        AND MatchID = ip_MatchID
      
      **Purpose**:
      - Remove from queue
      - Prevent reprocessing
      - Track completion
    end note
    
    CTS_DB --> DataAccess: Success
    deactivate CTS_DB
    
    DataAccess --> Service: Complete
    deactivate DataAccess
    
end

Service --> JobService: Complete
deactivate Service

== Job Complete ==

JobService --> Controller: Return true
deactivate JobService

Controller --> Scheduler: 200 OK (Success)
deactivate Controller

note over Scheduler
  **Next Run (5 minutes later)**:
  - Will pick next match in queue
  - FIFO order maintained
  - Process ONE match at a time
end note

@enduml

